    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** (82.97) and **Junior Caminero** (71.00) standing as our clear focal points. **Yordan Alvarez** benefits from a highly favorable matchup against Gil (xERA 5.74), providing the highest raw ceiling in the lineup, while **Junior Caminero**\u2019s position in the #2 hole against Woods Richardson offers elite run-production potential. We are also looking for a strong performance from **Luke Raley** (57.91), who leverages a solid platoon advantage and park factors to outperform his base projection. Conversely, while **Victor Scott II** (53.24) and **Hyeseong Kim** (48.31) lack elite raw power, their sprint speed remains vital to our strategy, despite **Hyeseong Kim** facing the challenge of Imanaga\u2019s elite skill set and a difficult platoon matchup.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Chase Meidroth**, whose 44.54 score fell just short of the active roster. While **Chase Meidroth** benefits from a strong #1 batting order assignment, his marginal efficiency against Griffin makes him a sub-optimal start relative to the rest of the infield depth. We also continue to monitor the \"Lineup Pending\" status for **Caleb Durbin**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, **Carson Benge**, and **Jerar Encarnacion**. While we have modeled the lineup with assumed batting positions, any late changes\u2014particularly regarding **Caleb Durbin**\u2014could shift his aggressive park-factor advantage. Risk management remains paramount today, as **Trea Turner** and **Kyle Schwarber** face the formidable arm of Sale; their scores (54.65 and 52.96 respectively) are dampened by Sale\u2019s elite xERA of 2.88, making them high-leverage plays that rely heavily on their dynamic hitting profiles to overcome the pitcher\u2019s skill advantage.",
